\begin{hxmodule2}{LabelInsideOutside}{PUT ONE SENTENCE SUMMARY HERE}

\hxlabel{HxLabelInsideOutside}
\hxfeatureid{HxLabelInsideOutside}

\begin{hxdescription}
 The \textit{LabelInsideOutside} module adds a new label
 group "\textit{Location}" including the labels "\textit{inside}"
 and "\textit{outside}". All components are labeled to
 inside or outside depending on there position related to
 the root node and base nodes.\\
 If there is a base node on the shortest path from the
 component to the root node, the component is labeled as
 "\textit{outside}" and "\textit{inside}" otherwise. Roots
 are classified as inside whereby base nodes are related to
 the outside.
 
\end{hxdescription}

\begin{hxconnections}
\hxlabel{HxLabelInsideOutside_data}
\hxport{Data}{\tt [required]}\\
 The module requires a spatial graph with following label
 groups:
 \begin{itemize}
 \item Time Step
 \item Node Type with labels
       \{TIP_NODE, BRANCHING_NODE, BASE_NODE, ROOT_NODE\}
 \end{itemize}

\end{hxconnections}

\end{hxmodule2}
